To finalize the connection between your website and the Google Sheet, follow these steps:

### 1. Google Apps Script Setup (Action Required)
You must deploy the bridge script first. 
1. Open your [Google Sheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Dfe350SALDp9bz8oXA9xKtomCwWbTVvvDJLMC1zZg6Y).
2. Go to **Extensions > Apps Script**.
3. Delete any existing code and paste this:
```javascript
function doPost(e) {
  try {
    var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.openByUrl("https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Dfe350SALDp9bz8oXA9xKtomCwWbTVvvDJLMC1zZg6Y").getSheets()[0];
    var data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);

    // Column Mapping: Date | Name | Contact Number | Gender | Roadmap
    sheet.appendRow([
      new Date(), 
      data.name, 
      "'" + (data.contact || data.phone), // Prefix with ' to treat as string in Sheets
      data.gender, 
      data.roadmap
    ]);

    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({"result": "success"}))
      .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
